{"type":"message","id":"46edf103","parentId":"5e1cdf1e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:53:38.887Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y5tddt6tjnzh_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125214\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n1. Phase 1 COMPLETE for Architecture cross-analysis\r\n2. Gap-Decay Synthesis complete\r\n3. LLM-Augmented Pulse complete\r\n4. CFI Compression Experiment complete - major finding about constant format tokens\r\n\r\nThe key pending item is: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nFrom the synthesis document:\r\n- Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe insight that compression objective is: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI should implement and run this experiment. Let me check what data I have available and run the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse, the last one was `pulse_2026-03-24 125117.md`. I need to run the next pulse which should include the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, the instruction says to do ONE concrete action. Let me think about what would advance the goals most effectively:\r\n\r\n1. Run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment - this is explicitly listed as the next experiment\r\n2. Create a Python script to implement the scoring function and analyze the data\r\n3. Update the goals file with progress\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create and run the hybrid scoring experiment. I should:\r\n1. Create a Python script that implements score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Analyze the existing pulse data with this scoring\r\n3. Document the results\r\n\r\nLet me create a script to run this experiment and analyze the results.\r\n\r\nWait - I need to check what data files exist. The CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md mentions running an experiment on 200 pulses with 80/20 split. \r\n\r\nI'll craft a targeted analysis script to validate the hybrid scoring approach. The script will focus on implementing the precise scoring function and extracting key insights about token scoring. I'll ensure the implementation follows the exact mathematical specification from the synthesis document, carefully parsing and calculating scores for each token.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified the need for hybrid CFI×Freq scoring, with a concrete formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). The next logical action is to implement this scoring and run the experiment to validate whether it correctly distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory.\"\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run a Python script implementing the hybrid scoring formula to analyze pulse tokens, testing whether CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring better separates metaprogramming artifacts from meaningful research tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nHybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\nTest: score(T) = CFI(T) × sqrt(min(freq, 120)/30)\r\n\r\nGoal: Better separate constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi: float, freq: int) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"CFI × sqrt(freq/30) with cap at freq=120\"\"\"\r\n    freq_normalized = min(freq, 120) / 30\r\n    return cfi * math.sqrt(freq_normalized)\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    pulse_dir = Path(\"pulses\")\r\n    token_stats = {}\r\n    \r\n    # Collect token statistics across all pulses\r\n    for pulse_file in sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[:200]:\r\n        content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n        tokens = content.split()\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            if token not in token_stats:\r\n                token_stats[token] = {\"count\": 0, \"pulses\": 0}\r\n            token_stats[token][\"count\"] += 1\r\n            token_stats[token][\"pulses\"] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate CFI (Conditional Frequency Index) and hybrid scores\r\n    results = []\r\n    total_pulses = 200\r\n    for token, stats in token_stats.items():\r\n        freq = stats[\"count\"]\r\n        cfi = freq / total_pulses  # Simple frequency-based CFI approximation\r\n        score = hybrid_score(cfi, freq)\r\n        results.append({\r\n            \"token\": token,\r\n            \"freq\": freq,\r\n            \"cfi\": round(cfi, 4),\r\n            \"score\": round(score, 4)\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    # Sort by score descending\r\n    results.sort(key=lambda x: x[\"score\"], reverse=True)\r\n    \r\n    print(\"=== TOP 20 TOKENS BY HYBRID SCORE ===\")\r\n    print(f\"{'Token':<40} {'Freq':>6} {'CFI':>8} {'Score':>8}\")\r\n    print(\"-\" * 65)\r\n    for r in results[:20]:\r\n        print(f\"{r['token']:<40} {r['freq']:>6} {r['cfi']:>8.4f} {r['score']:>8.4f}\")\r\n    \r\n    print(\"\\n=== FREQ > 100 TOKENS (constant-format candidates) ===\")\r\n    high_freq = [r for r in results if r[\"freq\"] > 100]\r\n    for r in high_freq:\r\n        print(f\"{r['token']:<40} {r['freq']:>6} {r['cfi']:>8.4f} {r['score']:>8.4f}\")\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"\\n=== SUMMARY ===\")\r\n    print(f\"Total unique tokens: {len(results)}\")\r\n    print(f\"High-frequency (>100): {len(h\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:52:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371218882}}
